cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about deep architectures for neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses various architectural variants and evaluates their performance, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of RNNs, which are commonly used in NLP and fall under the category of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a dataset of news translations, which involves image and text processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
